name: Cementerio de Recolta
description: The main entrance is a portico formed by four Greek Doric columns, completed during one of its great reforms ordered in 1881 by the then mayor of the Municipality, Torcuato de Alvear.

name: Mercado de Pulgas de San Telmo
description: Every Sunday you can browse and see antiques. Its core is in Plaza Dorrego and extends through the neighboring streets. The market comes alive even more, with musical performances, living statues, many cafes and restaurants where you can refuel after shopping.

name: Jhony Cay
description: Johnny Cay, also known locally as Islote Sucre, is the largest and most important key near San Andrés Island. Such is its importance that it was named a protected Regional Park, thanks to its biodiversity and beauty. It is a paradise that every tourist should know in the archipelago.

name: Rocky Cay
description: Rocky Cay, or Cayo Rocoso in Spanish, is another of the most visited places of interest in San Andrés. Its main attraction is that, unlike the other nearby islets, the ground is made up of rocks, less sand. Thus, it offers natural pools of crystal clear water so that you can relax like never before.

name: Santuario Dom Bosco
description: Beautiful church located on the north side (wing) of Brasilia. Don Bosco is undoubtedly one of the most beautiful churches in the federal capital. With high ceilings and it's lush blue tint it's hard not to be so beautiful.

name: Plaza de la Torre de TV
description: The Brasilia TV tower, apart from being a television transmission tower, has a panoramic viewpoint 75 meters high that is free.
